    "instructions": "1. Derive the general De Giorgi exponent formula for a dissipative PDE with diffusion order $s$ in dimension $n$. This typically involves scaling analysis of the nonlinear term vs. the dissipative term (e.g., $\\alpha = \\frac{n}{2s} + \\dots$ or similar scaling relations). \n2. For each of the following PDEs, identify their specific $n$ and $s$ and calculate/verify their exponent: \n   - 3D Navier-Stokes ($n=3, s=1$)\n   - 2D Navier-Stokes ($n=2, s=1$)\n   - 1D Burgers ($n=1, s=1$)\n   - SQG (Surface Quasi-Geostrophic) (identify $s$ for critical/subcritical cases)\n   - MHD (Magnetohydrodynamics) (identify $n$ and $s$)\n   - Fractional Navier-Stokes (general $s$)\n3. Ensure the final output provides the general formula and a clear verification table for all 6 cases.",
